This paper deals with the problem of obfuscating texts while preserving their content, which is a common task in natural language processing. The paper combines ideas from differential privacy and machine learning techniques for text processing, which are typical topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
